The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                     Running, skipping improve footwork

 - Focus on the spot you want the ball to land

  CRICKET ONLINE - RAVI SHASTRI
                             
	I am a leg-spinner. I often fail to maintain line and length and so prove to be expensive. Please help.
       
	(Ryan Mullick, 19, Calcutta-26)
       
	It is a difficult art that demands a lot of practice. Get the basics right with your coach.
       
	I am a right-handed batsman. I often fail to pick the right ball while driving off the back foot. Please advise.
       
	(Tuhin Bose, 14, Calcutta-19)
       
	Your are obviously not watching the ball closely enough. Hence youre messing up with your footwork.
       
	I am a right-handed batsman. I would like to know the ideal length to play the cover drive. Please advise.
       
	(Vishal Chawla, 19, Howrah)
       
	The ball thats over pitched just outside off-stump. 
       
	I am a right-arm medium-pacer. How does one bowl the off and leg cutters?
       
	(Ayan Mukherjee, 15, Calcutta-40)
       
	By moving your fingers clock and anti-clockwise across the seam.
       
	I often hit the ball into the air when trying to drive over-pitched deliveries. Please help.
       
	(Suhrid Dutta, 18, Calcutta)
       
	Get closer to the pitch of the ball and keep your head down.
       
	I am a right-handed batsman. Please advise me on some physical drills to improve my footwork.
       
	(Roktim Raha, 19, Calcutta)
       
	Lots of running and skipping will help.
       
	I am an off-spinner. Whenever I try to bowl a flighted delivery, it ends up being a full toss. Please help.
       
	(Sanjay Dutta, 16, Jamshedpur)
       
	Look at the spot you want the ball to land.
       
	While attempting the cut, I try to keep the ball down but often end up giving a catch to gully. Please help.
       
	(Sudip Roy, 21, Calcutta)
       
	Role your wrist when making contact with the ball.
       
	I am a right-handed batsman and often get bowled round the legs when playing the sweep against off-spinners. Please help.
       
	(Sarbajit Kundu, 19, Calcutta)
       
	Pick the right line and dont go too far across with your front foot.
       
	My 13-year-old son has just started playing. Should he start with a light or heavy bat?
       
	(Rupa Sen, 41, Calcutta-17)
       
	Light medium-sized bat will be ideal.
                                                                                  
